{
  "text": "Extending from general anchor-based methods, rotating default boxes [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] are used, with predicted rotation offset. Similarly, rotating region proposals [CITATION_3] are generated with 6 different orientations. Regression-based methods [CITATION_4] , [CITATION_5] , [CITATION_6] predict the rotation and positions of vertexes, which are insensitive to orientation. Further, in Liao et al. [CITATION_7] , rotating filters [CITATION_8] are incorporated to model orientation-invariance explicitly. The peripheral weights of 3 \u00d7 3 filters rotate around the center weight, to capture features that are sensitive to rotation.",
  "correct_citation": {
